      "body_md": "## AuditToolkit Linux Host Lite — v0.1.0\n\nGPG-signed Linux packages for host security auditing.\n\n### Artifacts\n| File | Format | Notes |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `audittoolkit-linux-lite_0.1.0.deb` | Debian/Ubuntu | + `.asc` detached signature |\n| `audittoolkit-linux-lite-0.1.0-1.noarch.rpm` | RHEL/Rocky/Fedora | + `.asc`; rpm header also GPG-signed |\n| `audittoolkit-linux-lite-0.1.0.tar.gz` | portable tarball | + `.asc` |\n\n### Signing & verification\nAll packages are signed by **AuditToolkit Release Signing `<release@audittoolkitlabs.com>`**\n(GPG fingerprint `36B9 C843 1CB4 4735 11E2 5D02 D9ED E688 AB61 1412`, published in `KEYS`).\n\n```bash\ngpg --import KEYS\ngpg --verify audittoolkit-linux-lite_0.1.0.deb.asc audittoolkit-linux-lite_0.1.0.deb\nsha256sum -c SHA256SUMS\n```\n\nA `Good signature from \"AuditToolkit Release Signing\"` confirms authenticity and integrity.\n\n### Install\n```bash\nsudo dpkg -i audittoolkit-linux-lite_0.1.0.deb       # Debian/Ubuntu\nsudo rpm -i  audittoolkit-linux-lite-0.1.0-1.noarch.rpm   # RHEL/Rocky\naudittoolkit-linux-lite run\n```\n",
